Recent years have seen significant increases in contraceptive use with many women able to achieve a 12-month injectable contraceptive. Current population stands at 734,250 with a projected 42% life expectancy at birth in 2011 with the total fertility rate at 4.3 births per woman. The abortion rate in the country is not known and may be as high as 220,000 each year.

Questions over the legality of abortion continues to be a contentious and difficult issue in Comoros. Those seeking an abortion while living in Comoros could run the risk of being penalized if the pregnancy were to be terminated. It is important to keep in mind the laws of abortion varies in different nationals of the country so it would be best to make sure that you will not run into any issues.

For further details on abortion in Comoros and other countries, please refer to our materials which can be downloaded from Abortion Garments page. Contraceptive, Reproductive and Sexual Health Information available for Comoros can be retrieved from Abortion Europages.
